HEADWORD: Monoecia
<hw>Mo*noe"ci*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <?/ house.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A Linnaean class of plants, whose stamens and pistils are in
distinct flowers in the same plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

